{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/49816", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/49816/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/49816/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/49816/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/49816", "id": 312677595, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWUzMTI2Nzc1OTU=", "number": 49816, "title": "Consider adding starts_with method for OsStr", "user": {"login": "Kixunil", "id": 1178779, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjExNzg3Nzk=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1178779?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/Kixunil", "html_url": "https://github.com/Kixunil", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Kixunil/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Kixunil/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Kixunil/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Kixunil/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Kixunil/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Kixunil/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Kixunil/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Kixunil/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Kixunil/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2018-04-09T20:35:03Z", "updated_at": "2018-04-09T22:06:43Z", "closed_at": "2018-04-09T22:06:43Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "When parsing arguments, one often wants to know whether the argument starts with \"--\" or \"-\". At the same time, `args_os()` is more robust approach because it allows specifying all paths OS allows.\r\n\r\nHowever, since there's no starts_with method, this is impossible on Windows and requires OsStrExt trait with converting to byte slice on Unix. An imperfect workaround would be attempting to convert to `&str` and assume false if conversion fails (hoping argument names are sane - not containing non-ASCII chars).\r\n\r\nSimilarly, `ends_with` could be added.\r\n\r\nI hope this doesn't need RFC, since it should be a very small and easy change.\r\n\r\nAnother thing that comes to my mind: arguments like `--foo=bar` can't be parsed - this requires slicing too.", "closed_by": {"login": "Kixunil", "id": 1178779, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjExNzg3Nzk=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1178779?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/Kixunil", "html_url": "https://github.com/Kixunil", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Kixunil/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Kixunil/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Kixunil/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Kixunil/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Kixunil/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Kixunil/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Kixunil/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Kixunil/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Kixunil/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/49816/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/49816/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": "completed"}